">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Quotation</span>.<span class=\"name\">precheck</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Quotation/Precheck.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Quotation.Precheck\">Precheck</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Quotation/Precheck.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Quotation.precheck","kind":"opaque","line":59,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Quotation.precheck","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/Quotation/Precheck.lean#L59-L89"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Quotation/Precheck.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Quotation.precheckAttribute\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Quotation</span>.<span class=\"name\">precheckAttribute</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/KeyedDeclsAttribute.html#Lean.KeyedDeclsAttribute\">KeyedDeclsAttribute</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Quotation/Precheck.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Quotation.Precheck\">Precheck</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Registers a double backtick syntax quotation pre-check.\n\n`@[quot_precheck k]` registers a declaration of type `Lean.Elab.Term.Quotation.Precheck` for the\nsyntax node kind `k`. It should implement eager name analysis on the passed syntax by throwing an\nexception on unbound identifiers, and calling `precheck` recursively on nested terms, potentially\nwith an extended local context (`withNewLocal`). Macros without registered precheck hook are\nunfolded, and identifier-less syntax is ultimately assumed to be well-formed.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Quotation/Precheck.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Quotation.precheckAttribute","kind":"opaque","line":41,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Quo